By Esther Egbe
MFM FC and U-23 Assistant Coach told National Daily that Nigeria Professional League players are the ones suffering as a result of the power tussle at the NFF Glass House.
Coach Fidelis Ilechukwu spoke on six of his team’s first choice players who had to move on during the mid-season window in a bid to seek greener pastures.
He decried the lack of experienced replacements but was confident that the team who cope well to achieve its aim for the season.
He concluded by hinting that another of his players, Chukwuemeka Onuwa, could also be on his way out in search of a better club.
 
